sphere /sfɪə/

(spheres) 

1. N-COUNT A sphere is an object that is completely round in shape like a ball. 球体 

例： Because the earth spins, it is not a perfect sphere. 因为地球旋转，所以它不是个完完全全的球体。 

2. N-COUNT A sphere of activity or interest is a particular area of activity or interest. (活动、兴趣的) 领域 

例： ...the sphere of international politics. …国际政治领域。

